\f0\fs24 \cf0 \uc0\u55357 \u56524  
\f1 January 8, 1642\

\f0 \
\uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f2 Today is the anniversary of the death of Galileo Galilei, the famous 
\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56814 \u55356 \u56825 
\f2 Italian genius (
\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
1564-1642), {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 astronomer}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Engineer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 engineer}}, sometimes described as a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polymath"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 polymath}}, from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pisa"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Pisa}}.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super  
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub Galileo has been called the "father of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Observational_astronomy"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 observational astronomy}}\'94, the "father of modern physics", the "father of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_method"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 scientific method}}", and the "father of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modern_science"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 modern science}}".\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Galileo studied {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speed"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 speed}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Velocity"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 velocity}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gravity"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 gravity}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_fall"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 free fall}}, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Principle_of_relativity"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 principle of relativity}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inertia"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 inertia}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Projectile_motion"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 projectile motion}} and also worked in applied science and technology, describing the properties of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pendulums"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 pendulums}} and "{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrostatic"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 hydrostatic}} balances", inventing the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermoscope"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 thermoscope}} and various {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sector_(instrument)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 military compasses}}, and using the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telescope"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 telescope}} for scientific observations of celestial objects.
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
